The '''2010 [[Showtime Southern 500]]''' at [[Darlington Raceway]] in [[Darlington, South Carolina]] was the eleventh race of the 2010 [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series]] season. The race began at 7:30 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] on May 8, 2010. The race was televised on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] and broadcasted on [[Motor Racing Network|MRN radio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/|title=NASCAR Sprint Cup Series Race Schedule and Time|publisher=NASCAR.com|accessdate=8 April 2010}}</ref> The race began with [[Jamie McMurray]] in the [[pole position]], while during the race there were 11 different leaders, 22 lead changes, and 11 cautions.<ref name="south" /> The Showtime Southern 500 winner was [[Denny Hamlin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/motor/nascar/2010-05-09-denny-hamlin-sprint-darlington-showtime-500_N.htm|title=Denny Hamlin wins 2010 Southern 500|date=9 May 2010|publisher=Nate Ryan|accessdate=11 May 2010|location=[[USA Today]]}}</ref>

== Practices and qualifying ==
There were only two practice sessions on May 7, 2010. In the first practice, [[A. J. Allmendinger]], [[Dave Blaney]], [[Mike Bliss]], [[Michael McDowell]], and [[Denny Hamlin]] were the fastest drivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/11/data/practice1_speeds.html|title=Practice 1 Results|date=7 May 2010|accessdate=7 May 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref> In the second practice session, [[Jamie McMurray]], Denny Hamlin, [[Kurt Busch]], [[Ryan Newman]], and [[Juan Pablo Montoya|Juan Montoya]] were the top five in speed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/11/data/practice2_speeds.html|title=Practice 2 Results|date=7 May 2010|accessdate=7 May 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref> During qualifying, Jamie McMurray won his second [[pole position]] in 2010 and set a new track record, while [[Jeff Gordon]], [[Brian Vickers]], [[David Reutimann]], and [[Mark Martin]]  also qualified to start in the first five positions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gQsgM4OLk8XJ95KhHdgItXmFgBngD9FI9NDG0|title=McMurray Sets Record|date=7 May 2010|publisher=Pete Iacobelli|accessdate=8 May 2010|location=[[Google.com]]}}</ref> There were three drivers who did not make the race: [[Joe Nemechek]], [[Casey Mears]], and Mike Bliss.<ref name="qual" />
[[File:JamieMcMurrayBristolAugust2007.jpg|thumb|180px|left|Pole Position winner [[Jamie McMurray]]]]

==Race summary==
To begin the pre-race ceremonies, Ken Sandifer, pastor at First Baptist Church of Darlington, delivered the invocation. Then, John Norman and Kenneth Shelton, from Pope Air Force Base, sang the [[U.S. National Anthem|national anthem]]. To start the engines, [[Michael Waltrip]] introduced the mothers of the drivers; the mothers said the command, "Sons and gentlemen, start your engines!"<ref name="racing">{{cite web|url=http://www.nascar.com/2010/races/lapbylap/05/08/lap.by.lap.darlington/index.html#viewSingle96841449|title=Race Summary|date=8 May 2010|accessdate=9 May 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref>

On the start, [[Jamie McMurray]] led them to the [[Racing_flags#The_green_flag|green flag]], but [[Jeff Gordon]] passed him to lead the first lap. Gordon led until lap 38, then, [[Brian Vickers]] claimed the lead. Seven laps later, on lap 45, the first [[Caution_Flag#The_yellow_flag|caution]] came out because [[Michael McDowell]] collided with the [[SAFER barrier|wall]] in turn two. During the [[pit stop]]s, Jamie McMurray reclaimed the first psition. On the [[Rolling start (Motorsport)|restart]], McMurray led them to the green flag. On lap 53, the second caution came out because [[Bobby Labonte]] and [[Joey Logano]] both spun out. McMurray led them to the green flag, and he led until lap 62; then the third caution came out.<ref name="racing" /> The caution was caused by [[Paul Menard]] spinning on the backstretch. The top-ten drivers did not pit under this caution, which resulted in McMurray leading on the restart on lap 66. On lap 83, the fourth caution came out because of a multiple car spin; the drivers involved were [[Greg Biffle]], [[Martin Truex, Jr.]], and [[Jimmie Johnson]], all with minor damage to the cars.[[Image:DennyHamlinAugust2007.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Race winner [[Denny Hamlin]] in 2007.]] After all lead lap cars pitted, [[Tony Stewart]] led the field to the green flag  on lap 88. Three laps later, Jeff Gordon reclaimed the lead. Jeff Gordon led up to the green flag pit stops on laps 121 to 154. The leaders in between pit stops were [[Denny Hamlin]], [[Kevin Harvick]], and [[Scott Speed]]; after the pit stops Hamlin reclaimed the lead. On lap 171, debris in the second turn caused the fifth caution. During pit stops, Jamie McMurray came off pit road first, which made him the new leader on the restart.<ref name="racing" />

Two laps later, on lap 180, the sixth caution came out because [[Kevin Conway (NASCAR)|Kevin Conway]] collided with the wall. Also during the caution, [[A. J. Allmendinger]]'s brakes failed, making him to decide to go down on the track apron, but his car turned sideways, went backwards, and collided into the driver's door of Jimmie Johnson. Both were uninjured, but the crash put them out of the race. On lap 190, McMurray brought the field to the green flag. Ten laps later, on lap 200, Tony Stewart spun on the backstretch to bering out the seventh caution. The restart happened on lap 204, with Jamie McMurray in the lead.<ref name="racing" /> 

Two laps later, [[Kyle Busch]] passed McMurray to lead for the first time. On lap 227, the eighth caution came out; Bobby Labonte collided the wall after blowing a tire on the backstretch. All the lead lap cars pitted, and [[David Reutimann]] was the first off pit road. On lap 233, Reutimann led the field to the green flag, but, one lap later, debris caused the ninth caution to come out. The cause for the debris on the track was when Martin Truex Jr. had a poor restart,  causing the rest of the field to get congested, which caused [[David Ragan]] to collide with the wall. On lap 237, [[Jeff Burton]] led them to the green flag. Burton lad until Jeff Gordon passed him on lap 261. Twenty laps later, Bobby Labonte and [[David Gilliland]] collided, and hit the wall. On lap 283, the lead lap cars pitted, and Kyle Busch won the race off pit road. Kyle Busch led the field on the restart, on lap 286.<ref name="racing" />

Three laps later, on lap, 189, Denny Hamlin passed Kyle Busch. Hamlin led until lap 341, when Jeff Burton passed him. Also, on the same lap, the eleventh caution came out because Joey Logano spun coming out of pit road. After the lead lap cars pitted, Denny Hamlin led them on the restart on lap 347. Denny Hamlin kept the lead, to sweep both the [[Nationwide Series]] and the [[Sprint Cup Series]] races.<ref name="racing" />

On May 12, after final inspection after the race, Michael McDowell and [[Robby Gordon]] were penalized 25 owner's points and $25,000 each for violations. Drivers Michael McDowell and Robby Gordon lost 25 drivers points. The reasons for the penalty were unapproved rear gear and for unapproved door braces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nascar.com/2010/news/headlines/cup/05/12/darlington.penalty.cup.rgordon.mmcdowell/index.html |title=Race Penalties |first= |last= |author= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=13 May 2010 |month=May |year=2010 |work= |publisher= |location=NASCAR.com |page= |pages= |at= |language= |trans_title= |format= |doi= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |accessdate=13 May 2010 |quote= |ref= |separator= |postscript= }}</ref>

